==French==
===Etymology===
Old French [[mastin]], from Vulgar Latin ''*mansuetīnus'' ‘tamed (animal)’, from Latin [[mansuetus]] ‘tamed’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/matɛ̃/}}

===Noun===
'''mâtin''' {{m}}
# [[guard dog]], [[watchdog]], [[hound]]
# ''(colloquial)'' sly old dog, cunning devil

====Derived Terms====
* [[mâtineau]]

===Interjection===
'''mâtin'''
# ''(archaic)'' Good Lord!, I say!

